@* OnInitializedAsync (decision 156): the sync prefix runs before the first paint ("loading"),
   the continuation after the await writes the signal and the effects re-render ("loaded") --
   Blazor's StateHasChanged-per-continuation, expressed by the signal graph. *@

<p id="out">@msg</p>

@code {
    private string msg = "idle";

    protected override async Task OnInitializedAsync()
    {
        msg = "loading";
        await Task.Delay(1);
        msg = "loaded";
    }
}
